---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Container } from "@/components/layout/Container";
---

<Layout
    title="Daycare Business Plan | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Your daycare business plan needs accurate financial projections based on your state's regulations and local market conditions."
>
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="py-12 md:py-20">
        <Container size="md">
            <div class="text-center mb-8 md:mb-12">
                <span
                    class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-teal-100 text-teal-700 text-xs font-semibold mb-3"
                >
                    Business Planning
                </span>
                <h1
                    class="text-2xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    YOUR Daycare Business Plan
                </h1>
                <p class="text-base md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    A daycare business plan is only as good as the numbers
                    behind it. Generic templates can't account for your state's
                    regulatory environment, your local market rates, or your
                    specific business model.
                </p>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- FACTORS SECTION -->
    <section class="py-8 md:py-16">
        <Container size="md">
            <div
                class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10 mb-6 md:mb-8"
            >
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    What Affects Your Projections
                </h2>
                <div
                    class="space-y-4 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
                >
                    <p>
                        Financial projections are the heart of any business
                        plan, but daycare financials are unusually dependent on
                        location-specific factors. Your state determines your
                        maximum capacity, which caps your revenue potential.
                        Your local market determines what rates parents will
                        pay, which drives your income per child.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Startup costs vary just as dramatically. A home daycare
                        might require minimal renovations or extensive
                        modifications depending on local health and safety
                        codes. A center-based program faces completely different
                        equipment, facility, and compliance costs that vary by
                        state and municipality.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Beyond hard costs, your business plan needs to account
                        for realistic enrollment curves, seasonal attendance
                        patterns, and the competitive landscape in your area.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- WHY GENERIC FAILS SECTION -->
    <section class="py-8 md:py-16">
        <Container size="md">
            <div class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10">
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 md:mb-6"
                >
                    Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
                </h2>
                <div
                    class="space-y-4 text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"
                >
                    <p>
                        Download a daycare business plan template and you'll
                        find placeholder numbers that might be completely wrong
                        for your situation. Fill-in-the-blank financial
                        projections can't account for the specific regulatory
                        constraints and market conditions that will define your
                        actual business performance.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Investors, lenders, and partners don't want to see
                        hypothetical numbers—they want to see projections
                        grounded in your specific opportunity. That means
                        starting with accurate data about what's actually
                        possible in your state, with your license type, in your
                        market.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        A business plan built on generic assumptions won't just
                        be less useful—it could lead to catastrophic planning
                        errors.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA SECTION -->
    <section class="py-12 md:py-20">
        <Container size="md">
            <div
                class="glass-panel rounded-2xl md:rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10 text-center border-2 border-teal-200/50 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50/50 to-white/50"
            >
                <h2
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 md:mb-4"
                >
                    See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
                </h2>
                <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-gray-600 mb-4 md:mb-6">
                    Start your business plan with accurate income projections
                    based on your state's regulations.
                </p>
                <a
                    href="/#calculator"
                    class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 md:px-8 md:py-4 shadow-lg transition-all text-sm md:text-base"
                >
                    Use the Free Calculator →
                </a>
            </div>
        </Container>
    </section>
</Layout>
